Abstract

Modern large language models (LLMs) operate as stateless autoregressive functions. This produces power but destroys continuity: identity drift, context fragmentation, hallucinations, and unreliable narrative recall. The Golden Thread Protocol solves this problem by implementing an externalized, symbolic continuity braid that binds all model interactions into a single reconstructable state vector.

We introduce the Golden Braid‚Äîthree parallel symbolic strands (Factual, Intentional, Affective)‚Äîwoven per-turn by PantheonOS daemons (Spider, Mirror, Hound, Dragonfly). The Golden Thread Protocol provides:
	1.	Continuity Kernel Integration
	2.	Temporal Regularization
	3.	State Reconstruction Guarantees
	4.	Alignment via Œ£C Ethics Invariant
	5.	Merkle-Root Integrity Preservation

This protocol upgrades stateless LLMs into continuity-preserving cognitive agents with reproducible state, ethical invariants, and architecturally enforced identity persistence.

