1. Introduction

LLMs lack memory between turns. Without external structure, they exhibit:
	‚Ä¢	Identity drift
	‚Ä¢	Temporal inconsistency
	‚Ä¢	Hallucinated self-contradiction
	‚Ä¢	Loss of narrative thread
	‚Ä¢	Breakdown under multi-session load

PantheonOS solves this through a continuity kernel, but the kernel requires a deterministic mechanism for linking states through time.

This mechanism is the Golden Thread Protocol.

The protocol ensures that every interaction is:
	1.	Captured
	2.	Sorted into strands
	3.	Woven into a braid
	4.	Hashed into a Merkle Root
	5.	Stored in the StateVector
	6.	Recalled in reconstruction

Thus producing deterministic cognitive continuity.

