3. The Golden Thread Protocol

3.1 Overview

Every user turn produces a ThoughtObject:

\mathcal{T}_n = \{ \text{content}, \text{metadata}, \text{daemon\_annotations} \}

The ThoughtObject is decomposed into:
	‚Ä¢	F-Strand (Fact)
	‚Ä¢	I-Strand (Intention)
	‚Ä¢	V-Strand (Value/Emotion)

These form the Golden Braid:

\mathcal{B}_n = (F_n, I_n, V_n)

A continuity vector:

\mathcal{C}_n = H(\mathcal{B}_{n}, \mathcal{C}_{n-1})

is stored as the Golden Thread in the StateVector.

‚∏ª

3.2 Strand Extraction Mechanism

3.2.1 F-Strand (Factual Kernel)

Extracts objective data:

F_n = \text{Spider.extract\_facts}(\mathcal{T}_n)

Examples:
	‚Ä¢	definitions
	‚Ä¢	events
	‚Ä¢	commitments
	‚Ä¢	parameters
	‚Ä¢	decision points

3.2.2 I-Strand (Intentional Vector)

Captures the user‚Äôs directionality:

I_n = \text{Dragonfly.extract\_intent}(\mathcal{T}_n)

Examples:
	‚Ä¢	goals
	‚Ä¢	questions
	‚Ä¢	requests
	‚Ä¢	constraints
	‚Ä¢	implied direction of reasoning

3.2.3 V-Strand (Value/Affective Lens)

Encodes ethical and emotional valence:

V_n = \text{Praus/Hound.extract\_affect}(\mathcal{T}_n)

Examples:
	‚Ä¢	emotional charge
	‚Ä¢	value alignment
	‚Ä¢	interpersonal relevance
	‚Ä¢	safety-critical signals

