3.4 Continuity Hash (Merkle Integration)

Define global continuity hash:

\mathcal{C}_n = H(\mathcal{B}_n \parallel \mathcal{C}_{n-1})

This produces a chain identical in structure to a blockchain but lightweight and local:
	‚Ä¢	tamper evident
